168         monitoring_script = f"""#!/bin/bash
169 # ACGS-PGP Database Monitoring Script
170 
171 DB_HOST="{self.db_config["host"]}"
172 DB_PORT="{self.db_config["port"]}"
173 DB_NAME="{self.db_config["database"]}"
174 DB_USER="{self.db_config["username"]}"
175 
176 echo "🔍 ACGS-PGP Database Health Check"
177 echo "================================="
178 
179 # Connection test
180 echo "1. Testing database connection..."
181 if pg_isready -h $DB_HOST -p $DB_PORT -U $DB_USER -d $DB_NAME; then
182     echo "  ✅ Database is accepting connections"
183 else
184     echo "  ❌ Database connection failed"
185     exit 1
186 fi
187 
188 # Database size
189 echo -e "\\n2. Database size information..."
190 psql -h $DB_HOST -p $DB_PORT -U $DB_USER -d $DB_NAME -c "
191 SELECT 
192     pg_database.datname as database_name,
193     pg_size_pretty(pg_database_size(pg_database.datname)) as size
194 FROM pg_database 
195 WHERE datname = '$DB_NAME';"
196 
197 # Table information
198 echo -e "\\n3. Table information..."
199 psql -h $DB_HOST -p $DB_PORT -U $DB_USER -d $DB_NAME -c "
200 SELECT 
201     schemaname,
202     tablename,
203     pg_size_pretty(pg_total_relation_size(schemaname||'.'||tablename)) as size,
204     pg_stat_get_tuples_inserted(c.oid) as inserts,
205     pg_stat_get_tuples_updated(c.oid) as updates,
206     pg_stat_get_tuples_deleted(c.oid) as deletes
207 FROM pg_tables pt
208 JOIN pg_class c ON c.relname = pt.tablename
209 WHERE schemaname = 'public'
210 ORDER BY pg_total_relation_size(schemaname||'.'||tablename) DESC;"
211 
212 # Active connections
213 echo -e "\\n4. Active connections..."
214 psql -h $DB_HOST -p $DB_PORT -U $DB_USER -d $DB_NAME -c "
215 SELECT 
216     count(*) as active_connections,
217     state,
218     application_name
219 FROM pg_stat_activity 
220 WHERE datname = '$DB_NAME'
221 GROUP BY state, application_name
222 ORDER BY active_connections DESC;"
223 
224 # Migration status
225 echo -e "\\n5. Migration status..."
226 docker-compose exec -T alembic-runner alembic current
227 
228 echo -e "\\n✅ Database health check complete"
229 """

13 def wait_for_postgres(host="localhost", port="5433", user="acgs_user", password="acgs_password", max_attempts=30):
14     """Wait for PostgreSQL to be ready"""
15     print(f"Waiting for PostgreSQL at {host}:{port}...")
16     
17     for attempt in range(max_attempts):
18         try:
19             # Use pg_isready if available, otherwise try psql
20             result = subprocess.run([
21                 "pg_isready", 
22                 "-h", host, 
23                 "-p", str(port), 
24                 "-U", user
25             ], capture_output=True, text=True)
26             
27             if result.returncode == 0:
28                 print("✅ PostgreSQL is ready!")
29                 return True
30                 
31         except FileNotFoundError:
32             # pg_isready not available, try psql
33             try:
34                 env = os.environ.copy()
35                 env["PGPASSWORD"] = password
36                 result = subprocess.run([
37                     "psql", 
38                     "-h", host, 
39                     "-p", str(port), 
40                     "-U", user, 
41                     "-d", "acgs_pgp_db",
42                     "-c", "SELECT 1;"
43                 ], capture_output=True, text=True, env=env)
44                 
45                 if result.returncode == 0:
46                     print("✅ PostgreSQL is ready!")
47                     return True
48                     
49             except FileNotFoundError:
50                 print("⚠️  Neither pg_isready nor psql found, trying Python connection...")
51                 try:
52                     import psycopg2
53                     conn = psycopg2.connect(
54                         host=host,
55                         port=port,
56                         user=user,
57                         password=password,
58                         database="acgs_pgp_db"
59                     )
60                     conn.close()
61                     print("✅ PostgreSQL is ready!")
62                     return True
63                 except Exception as e:
64                     pass
65         
66         print(f"⏳ Attempt {attempt + 1}/{max_attempts} - PostgreSQL not ready yet...")
67         time.sleep(2)
68     
69     print("❌ PostgreSQL failed to become ready")
70     return False
